title: Independent Candidate Aurangzeb Khan wins PK-94 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent Candidate Aurangzeb Khan has won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-94, Orakzai by securing 18,648 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was an Jamiat Ullema-e-Islam Pakistan (JUI) candidate Abdur Rehman who bagged 8,274 votes.
Overall voters turn-out remained 24.42 per cent.
